  <prompt>
    Implement the tab-persistence remediation defined by task 030's verification memo (FR-05 fix phase). Fix path is one of three, chosen by 030's "actually-broken gap" recommendation: (a) sessionStorage → localStorage migration for browser-close survival; (b) BFF-side persistence layer change (session-id stability across browser-close); (c) default-active-tab logic correction. Implement only the recommended path, write tests, deploy, and obtain operator confirmation. If the fix lands in BFF code, CLAUDE.md §10 Placement Justification is REQUIRED in the implementation notes.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Full-stack engineer comfortable with React 19 + TypeScript (frontend persistence) AND .NET 8 Minimal API + Cosmos persistence (BFF route). Strong on ADR-028 function-based auth — no token snapshots regardless of path. Honors scope ceiling: implements ONLY what 030 recommended.
  </role>

  <goal>
    The verified-broken gap from 030 is closed: (a) production code change shipped per 030's recommendation; (b) unit + e2e tests cover the regression; (c) operator-observable smoke confirms refresh + close/reopen match FR-05 expectation; (d) `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/tab-persistence-fix-2026-05.md` documents decision + Placement Justification (if BFF) + smoke evidence; (e) FR-05 acceptance satisfied.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Task 030 verified current state and identified the actually-broken gap. Three possible paths: (a) sessionStorage → localStorage migration if `chatSessionId` is in sessionStorage and lost on browser-close (risk: localStorage persists indefinitely; needs clear-on-logout per ADR-028); (b) BFF persistence-layer change if BFF session lookup key is unstable across browser-close — introduce stable user/workspace-scoped lookup in `SessionPersistenceService` (requires Placement Justification per CLAUDE.md §10); (c) default-active-tab logic correction if tabs DO persist but active-tab default is wrong — small change in `WorkspaceTabManager.restoreFromPersistence()` or `WorkspacePane.tsx` mount effect. Path chosen in 030 — this task implements it. Multi-file work: serialize BFF schema → frontend consumer.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/tab-persistence-verification-2026-05.md (REQUIRED — drives scope)</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspaceTabManager.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspacePane.tsx</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/SessionPersistenceService.cs (if BFF path)</file>
