      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/tab-persistence-fix-2026-05.md (NEW)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Function-based auth: `authenticatedFetch` from `@spaarke/auth` for every BFF call. NO token snapshots. If localStorage migration chosen, migrated key MUST NOT contain auth tokens.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">If BFF touched: stay within `Sprk.Bff.Api`; no new service; consume AI via `PublicContracts/` facade only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">No new BFF DI feature modules. Extend existing modules.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 only — no React 16 fallbacks.</constraint>
    <constraint source="root-CLAUDE.md §10">If any code lands in `Sprk.Bff.Api/`: Placement Justification REQUIRED in fix memo; verify publish size ≤60 MB compressed (NFR-01); cite `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-05 — operator-confirmed end-to-end behavior, not just unit-test green.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Scope ceiling: implement ONLY 030's recommended path. No "while I'm here" expansion. If 030's scope feels wrong, raise with operator.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">If localStorage introduced (path a): explicit clear-on-logout + NO PII/auth tokens (opaque ids only).</constraint>
  </constraints>

