  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Load 030 memo + confirm fix path">Read the verification memo end-to-end. Confirm the actually-broken gap is well-defined and the recommended path is one of (a/b/c). If unresolved questions remain, STOP and escalate per CLAUDE.md §6.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Design + Placement Justification">Sketch the minimal change (files, API contract, storage keys, or state-machine changes). Write design as opening section of `tab-persistence-fix-2026-05.md`. Include Placement Justification (REQUIRED if BFF) citing `bff-extensions.md` criteria.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Implement frontend (path a or c)">If (a): migrate storage key, add clear-on-logout, ensure no PII/tokens. If (c): modify `restoreFromPersistence()` or WorkspacePane mount effect for spec-correct default. JSDoc references FR-05. Do NOT mix paths.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement BFF (path b)">Modify `SessionPersistenceService` (+`StoredSession.cs` if schema change) for stable user/workspace-scoped lookup. Extend tabs[] schema additively. Update PATCH/GET routes preserving the endpoint filter chain (ADR-008). Register new DI in existing module (ADR-010).</step>
    <step order="5" name="Update frontend consumer (path b)">If path (b) shifted contract, update `WorkspacePane.tsx` to the new lookup key. Continue with `authenticatedFetch` (ADR-028). No token snapshots.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Write unit tests">Frontend: add cases to `__tests__/WorkspaceTabManager.test.ts`. BFF: add cases to `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Sessions/` covering new behavior + backwards-compat with existing Cosmos docs.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Build + test + publish-size">Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` (0 errors), `npm run build` in `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/`, `dotnet test`, `npm run test`. If BFF touched: `dotnet publish -c Release` and verify compressed size ≤60 MB (NFR-01); document delta in fix memo. If regressed, STOP and re-evaluate.</step>
    <step order="8" name="Operator smoke">Via `ui-test` skill or operator-driven, execute both acceptance scenarios: (A) refresh — 3 tabs restored + correct active tab; (B) close/reopen — behavior matches spec expectation per 030 memo. Document evidence in fix memo.</step>
    <step order="9" name="Quality gates (FULL rigor Step 9.5)">Invoke `/code-review` and `/adr-check` on changed files. Address HIGH-severity findings. Document gate output in fix memo.</step>
    <step order="10" name="Finalize fix memo">Complete the memo with: design decision (path + rationale + scope honored); Placement Justification (if BFF); files modified; test coverage; build + publish-size evidence; operator smoke; gate output; known limitations (no scope expansion).</step>
    <step order="11" name="Update TASK-INDEX + document deviations">Update TASK-INDEX.md row 031 → ✅ completed. Mark FR-05 satisfied if smoke confirmed, else `in-progress (awaiting operator smoke)`. If any deviation from 030's recommendation, document + escalate before merging.</step>
  </steps>

