  <ui-tests>
    <test name="Tab persistence across browser refresh (FR-05 / R3 NFR-09 regression)">
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?appid={app-id}&amp;pagetype=custom&amp;name=sprk_spaarkeai</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Sign in and navigate to SpaarkeAi; open 3 non-Home tabs via Context wizards (e.g., Create Matter, Create Project, Find Similar)</step>
        <step>Confirm Home + 3 non-Home tabs (4 total); note the active tab</step>
        <step>Press Ctrl+R / Cmd+R; wait for SpaarkeAi to fully load</step>
        <step>Verify all 3 non-Home tabs restored in same order; previously-active tab is still active</step>
        <step>Check browser console for telemetry errors (TELEMETRY_TAB_RESTORE_LOAD_FAILURE etc.)</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>All 3 non-Home tabs restored; active tab matches pre-refresh; no console errors.</expected>
    </test>

    <test name="Tab persistence across browser close/reopen (FR-05 / OC-R4-02 newly-uncovered scenario)">
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?appid={app-id}&amp;pagetype=custom&amp;name=sprk_spaarkeai</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Sign in, navigate to SpaarkeAi, open 3 non-Home tabs; note the active tab</step>
        <step>CLOSE the entire browser application (full window/process, not just the SpaarkeAi tab)</step>
        <step>Reopen the browser and navigate back to SpaarkeAi (may require re-auth); wait for full load</step>
        <step>Observe tab state vs spec expectation from 030 memo: if "tabs restored" → verify all 3 return; if "Home default" → verify only Home</step>
        <step>Check browser console for telemetry errors</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Behavior matches the spec expectation documented in 030's verification memo.</expected>
    </test>

    <test name="ADR-028 compliance (no token snapshots — regression guard)">
      <steps>
        <step>Open DevTools → Application → Storage; inspect sessionStorage + localStorage for keys matching `*token*` / `*bearer*` / `*spaarke*token*`</step>
        <step>Inspect React props in React DevTools for `accessToken` props on any component</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>No auth tokens in browser storage; no `accessToken` props (ADR-028 INV-3/INV-4).</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">030's memo exists and recommends a specific fix path; this task implements ONLY that path. Production code change shipped (minimal, focused diff) in `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/` and/or `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Unit tests added covering the behavior change. `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` and `npm run build` in `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/` succeed with 0 errors and no new warnings.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">If BFF touched: `dotnet publish` compressed size ≤60 MB (NFR-01); Placement Justification documented citing `bff-extensions.md` criteria; no new direct `IOpenAiClient` / `IPlaybookService` injections outside `Services/Ai/` (F-2 baseline preserved).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">ADR-028 invariants preserved: no `accessToken` props/state; all BFF calls use `authenticatedFetch`; no auth tokens in sessionStorage/localStorage.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Operator smoke confirms refresh + close/reopen match FR-05 spec expectation (evidence in fix memo). `/code-review` + `/adr-check` quality gates run; HIGH-severity findings addressed.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`tab-persistence-fix-2026-05.md` documents decision, Placement Justification (if BFF), files modified, test coverage, smoke evidence, gate output. TASK-INDEX.md row 031 → ✅ completed; FR-05 marked satisfied (or `in-progress` pending operator smoke).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Scope ceiling is load-bearing. R3 task 065 was a large multi-file rewrite; A-5b is a focused fix on the specific gap 030 identifies. Resist "while I'm here" expansion — broader refactors are R5 candidates. 030's memo IS the design doc; if unclear, escalate before writing code. Effort range by path: (c) ~2-3h frontend-only; (a) ~3-4h frontend + clear-on-logout; (b) ~5-8h BFF + frontend + Placement Justification + publish-size check. The 6h estimate covers the median. If path (b), serialize BFF→frontend per multi-file decomposition guidance — don't parallelize the halves.
  </notes>

